Mark FisherDave DouglasRebecca KelleyBeth Colburn




 Mark graduated from Capital University College of Law before teaming with David Douglas to form Fisher & Douglas, LLP. After bringing over twenty-five years of experience guiding clients through Family Law, Juvenile Law, Personal Injury, and Criminal Law, Mark will be retiring from the practice of law in 2015. Mark enjoys live music and raising his son, Raad and plans to do some creative writing in retirement.

Education: Bachelor of Arts, English—The Ohio State University (1974)
Juris Doctorate-Capital University College of Law (1980)
Employment: Fisher & Douglas, LLP—Partner (1987-Present)
Licensure: Ohio (1980)
Services: Family Law, Juvenile Law, Criminal Law.
Memberships: Columbus Bar Association
Community Services: The Community Festival (1988-Present)

 

 David graduated from Capital University College of Law before teaming with Mark Fisher to form Fisher & Douglas, LLP. He is licensed in Ohio, and has over twenty-five years of experience guiding clients through Business and Corporate Law, as well as Real Estate Law, with an emphasis on hotels and shopping centers. David was raised in Pittsburgh, the home of various ethnic groups. He enjoys coaching high school wrestlers and supporting the National Champion Ohio State Wrestling Team. If you stop by the office after-hours, you will hear him playing the piano. Dave also grows giant pumpkins, and placed third two years ago at the Circleville Pumpkin Show with a 1200-pound pumpkin.

Education: Bachelor of Arts, History & Archeology—Westminster College PA (1974) Overseas Studies—Pahlavi University, Shiraz, Iran (1971-72) Juris Doctorate—Capital University College of Law (1978)
Employment: Fisher & Douglas, LLP—Managing Partner (1987-Present)
Licensure: Ohio (1978), United States Tax Court (1987)
Services: Business & Corporate, Real Estate, Real Estate Planning, Probate & Estate Planning
Memberships: Ohio State Bar Association
Community Services:

