Chairman of the MORPC Local Government Committee
Local Government Committee (1983-1986)
Law Director, Minerva Park (1984-1988)


 

 Rebecca joined Fisher & Douglas after graduating from Capital University Law School. She has been admitted to practice in Ohio and in the United States District Court for the Southern District of Ohio. Rebecca has over 15 years experience representing businesses and commercial property owners as well as guiding families through the probate process.
Rebecca was born in Columbus and returned to the Columbus area while in the fifth grade. She moved to Grove City, Ohio in 2009. Outside of the office, Rebecca enjoys quilting, needlework, reading, hiking and backpacking. Recently, she was elected president of Grove City’s Fat Quarters Quilt Guild. Two of her favorite backpacking destinations are the Grand Canyon and Yosemite National Park. She is also an avid Cincinnati Reds fan.

Education: Bachelor of Arts, History – Capital University
Juris Doctorate – Capital University Law School
Employment: Fisher & Douglas, LLP – Partner (2009 to Present)
