 Beth is a Columbus, Ohio native and has been working in the legal field since 2002, with previous work at the Ohio State University Medical Center. Outside of work Beth enjoys cooking, and spending time with her husband, two teenaged sons and friends. Beth also volunteers her time as a referee coordinator for the recreational soccer league at the Grove City Kids Association.

Education: Bachelor of Science, Psychology—Mount Union College (1990)
Employment: Fisher & Douglas, LLP—Office Manager/Legal Secretary (2007-Present)

 
 
 
 

